HEADWORD: agnathan
<hw>agnathan</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an eel-shaped
vertebrate without jaws or paired appendages; a member of the
<class>Agnatha</class>. The group includes the cyclostomes and some
extinct forms.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> jawless vertebrate, jawless fish</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agnatic</ent>⟦br⟧
